## Adventure Works SQL Queries

# Overview

This repository contains SQL queries for the Adventure Works database. Adventure Works is a sample database provided by Microsoft that simulates a fictional bicycle company. The queries in this repository cover various aspects of database interactions, including data retrieval, modification, and analysis.

## Getting Started

1. Clone the Repository

   git clone https://github.com/Gideon-kipronoh/Adventure-works-sql-queries.git


2. Database Setup
   Ensure you have access to the Adventure Works database. You can download it from the [Microsoft GitHub repository](https://github.com/Microsoft/sql-server-samples/releases/tag/adventureworks).
   Attach the Adventure Works database to your SQL Server instance.

3. Run Queries
   Open your preferred SQL Server query tool (e.g., SQL Server Management Studio, Azure Data Studio).
   Execute the queries from the repository on the Adventure Works database.

Query Categories

1.Data Retrieval

select_customers.sql- Retrieve information about customers.
select_products.sql- Get details about the products in the Adventure Works catalog.
select_orders.sql -Fetch data related to customer orders.

2. Data Modification

update_prices.sql-Update product prices based on certain criteria.
insert_new_product.sql-Add a new product to the catalog.

3. Data Analysis

sales_analysis.sql- Analyze sales data to identify top-performing products and customers.
order_statistics.sql-Calculate various statistics related to orders.

# Contributing

Feel free to contribute additional queries or improvements. Follow these steps:

1. Fork the repository.
2. Create a new branch for your changes.
3. Make your modifications.
4. Submit a pull request with a clear description of your changes.

